               <floruit>Marina probably lived in the 5th century, and the first biographical account was probably written sometime between 525 and 650. She was a Christian who wanted to be a monk and dressed as a man. Not to be confused with <persName ref="PRS6741Marina">Marinā</persName> commemorated on
                  <date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Hamle23">23 Ḥamle</date>.
               </floruit>
               <note></note>
               <note type="commemoration">commemorated on <date ref="ethiocal:Nahase15">15 Nāḥase</date> and, together with her father Eugenius, on
                  <date ref="ethiocal:Tahsas8">8 Tāḫśāś</date></note>
